Funke Akindele-Bello’s creation, My siblings and I, will return for the fourth season in January 2022. The family sitcom, which follows the Aberuagba family, whose family mantra is ‘an Aberuagba’s business is every Aberuagba’s business,’ will premiere on Monday, January 10, 2022, on Africa Magic Urban. The last season ended on an exciting note as Aunty Blessing’s ‘boo’ asked her to marry him but then misplaced the engagement ring. The biggest question fans have to ask this season is – “will we be planning a wedding?”   Broda Shaggi promises to work harder in 2022     Shazam tips Ayra Starr for global recognition     Toke Makinwa: Bloggers obsessed with my ‘private part’   The sitcom, which has been acquired by Africa Magic, is one of the series and sitcoms scheduled for a new season in 2022. - Advertisement - Speaking on the new season of the sitcom, Executive Head, Content and West Africa Channels, MultiChoice Nigeria, Dr. Busola Tejumola, said: “Local content is at the heart of our production at Africa Magic. The returning Africa Magic series will tell the inclusive stories of Nigerian families with My Siblings and I. Fans of these series will be in for great entertainment this January 2022.” The new seasons join other Africa Magic series, Dilemma, Venge, Movement-Japa, and The Rishantes giving viewers a more diverse range of local stories to watch.